GOVERNMENT OF INDIA (BHARAT SARKAR)
CABINET SECRETARIAT (MANTRIMANDAL SACHIVALAYA)
New Delhi, the 24th May, 2003
3 Jyaistha, 1925(S)
The undersigned is directed to say that with effect from the 24th May, 2003 : -
Shri Anant Kumar relinquished the charge of the office of Minister of Rural
Development. He will continue to hold the charge of the office of Minister
of Urban Development and Poverty Alleviation.
i)
Shri Kashiram Rana relinquished the charge of the office of Minister of
Textiles and assumed the charge of the office of Minister of Rural
Development.
Shri Syed Shahnawaz Hussain relinquished the charge of the office of
Minister of Civil Aviation and assumed the charge of the office of Minister
of Textiles.
iii)
Shri Subodh Mohite assumed the charge of the office of Minister of Heavy
Industries and Public Enterprises.
iv)
Shri Rajnath Singh assumed the charge of the office of Minister of
Agriculture.
v)
Maj. Gen. (Retd.) B.C. Khanduri relinquished the charge of the office of
Minister of State (Independent charge) of the Ministry of Road Transport
and Highways and assumed the charge of the office of Minister of Road
Transport and Highways.
vi)
Shri Rajiv Pratap Rudi relinquished the charge of the office of Minister of
State in the Ministry of Commerce and Industry and assumed the charge
of the office of Minister of State (Independent charge) of the Ministry of
Civil Aviation.
vii)
Shri Vijay Goel relinquished the charge of the offices of Minister of State in
the Ministry of Parliamentary Affairs and Minister of State in the Ministry of
Labour and assumed the charge of the office of Minister of State in the
Ministry of Youth Affairs and Sports.
vii)
Shri Santosh Gangwar relinquished the charge of the office of Minister of
State in the Ministry of Petroleum and Natural Gas and assumed the
charge of the offices of Minister of State in the Ministry of Labour and
Minister of State in the Ministry of Parliamentary Affairs.
ix)
Smt. Sumitra Mahajan relinquished the charge of the office of Minister of
State in the Ministry of Communications and Information Technology and
assumed the charge of the office of Minister of State in the Ministry of
Petroleum and Natural Gas.
x)
